    "Evaluation": {
      "text": "Clinical diagnosis: skin nodules in characteristic sites, may have malodorous drainage\nDiagnosis may be difficult in the ED if single nodule is present.",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
    "Management": {
      "text": "Clindamycin\n1% topic\nAntibacterial soaps\nSystemic treatments (typically prescribed by specialist): acitretin, finasteride,\nprednisone\nIncision and drainage\nshould be avoided if possible due to risk of scarring\n[5]",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "Clindamycin",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Clindamycin"
